  "texts": [
    "First, there is no APP available that offers bidirectional translation for Auslan.",
    "Second, these applications lack the capability to correct mistakes because they cannot recognise and translate sign language effectively.",
    "Third, some applications necessitate users to have proficiency in English, which evidently poses a barrier for children who are still in the early stages of language acquisition.In the context of PODCs and CODAs, current Auslan communication and translation apps are unable to meet their flexible and individualized learning needs.",
    "Signers in communication are often facing the dilemma where they must choose between using sign language or written text.",
    "They cannot realistically pause an Auslan conversation to look up each gloss 5 in the dictionary for non-signers, and vice versa."
  ],
